(properties of integration)

Proschan (2016) . \(\mathcal{F}\)-measurable .

  1. Linearity: \(c_1\), \(c_2\) ,

  • \(\int \{ c_1 f_{1}(\omega) + c_2 f_{2}(\omega)\}d\mu (\omega) = c_1\int f_{1}(\omega)d\mu (\omega) + c_2\int f_{2}(\omega)d\mu (\omega)\) ( \(\infty - \infty\) \(-\infty + \infty\) )

  • \(E(c_1 X_1 + c_2 X_2) = c_1 E(X_1) + c_2 E(X_2)\) ( \(\infty - \infty\) \(-\infty + \infty\) )

  1. Integrable absolutely integrable

  • \(\int f(\omega) d\mu(\omega)\) \(\Leftrightarrow\) \(\int |f(\omega) | d\mu (\omega) <\infty\).

  • \(E(X)\) \(\Leftrightarrow\) \(E(|X|)<\infty\).

  1. Modulus inequality

  • \(|\int f(\omega) d\mu (\omega) | \leq \int |f(\omega)|d\mu(\omega)\).

  • \(|E(X)|\leq E(|X|)\).

  1. Preservation of ordering

  • \(f(\omega)\leq g(\omega)\) for \(\omega \notin N\), where \(\mu(N)=0\), then \(\int f(\omega)d\mu(\omega) \leq \int g(\omega)d\mu(\omega)\).

  • \(P(X\leq Y)=1\), then \(E(X)\leq E(Y)\).

  1. Integration term by term

  • If either \(f_n\) is nonnegative for all \(n\) or \(\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\int |f_{n}(\omega)|d\mu(\omega)<\infty\), then \(\int \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}f_{n}(\omega)d\mu(\omega) = \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}\int f_{n}(\omega)d\mu(\omega)\).

  • If either \(X_n\) is nonnegative for all \(n\) or \(\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}E(|X_n|)<\infty\), then \(E(\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}X_{n})=\sum_{n=1}^{\infty}E(X_n)\).
